properties.label: Neb.
properties.name: The ballot measure would permit individuals 18 years or older [minors with parental consent] to obtain a recommendation [from a physician or nurse practitioner] for medical cannabis to treat serious medical conditions.

properties.label: N.J.
properties.name: The Proposed Marijuana Legalization Amendment would amend the state constitution to legalize the recreational use of marijuana for adults age 21 and older. It would also legalize the cultivation, processing, and retail sales.

properties.label: S.D.
properties.name: Constitutional Amendment A would legalize the adult purchase and possession of cannabis. Initiated Measure 26 would legalize medical marijuana.

properties.label: Ariz.
properties.name: The Smart and Safe Act would legalize the possession of cannabis for Arizonans 21 years or older, and create a market for regulated sales.

properties.label: Miss.
properties.name: Initiative 65 would allow patients with qualifying conditions to use medical marijuana.

properties.label: Idaho
properties.name: The Idaho Medical Marijuana Act would legalize possession of marijuana for registered patients, and establish a legal framework for growing, production, testing and retail.
properties.sig_deadline: Unclear. Recent court ruling may allow campaign to file signatures after original May 1 deadline.

properties.label: Ore.
properties.name: Initiative 44, The Drug Addiction Treatment and Recovery Act, would remove criminal penalties for the personal, non-commercial possession of all drugs.

properties.label: Mont.
properties.name: Initiative 190 would legalize recreational marijuana, establish a regulatory framework for cultivation and sales, and tax it at a rate of 20%; Constitutional Initiative 118 sets the legal age for purchase, consumption, or possession at 21.
